There is a miscompilation issue report in LoopVectorize: 

C Testcase:
```c
long a, d;
short b[20];
short c[20];
_Bool e[20];
int f(_Bool g) {
  for (long h = 0; h < 16; h += g)
    b[h] = (short) g;
  for (int i = 0; i < 12; i++)
    for (int j = d; j; j++)
      c[i] = (short) a < e[i];
  return (int) b[0];
}
int main() {
  __builtin_printf("%X\n", f(1));
}
```
Godbolt: https://godbolt.org/z/3E8frs1Me

With loop-vectorize: `FFFFFFFF`
Without loop-vectorize: `1`

